## Why This Is Asked

This question tests the ability to design a tenant-scoped edge cache, ensure cross-DC coherence, and integrate with a docker-dca workflow including bootstrap commands and compose scaffolding.

## Key Concepts

- Per-tenant caching with tenant-scoped cache keys
- TTLs sourced from a central config service
- Cache invalidation on mutating requests and cross-DC coherence
- Edge proxy placement with TLS termination and header-based tenanting
- Observability and basic failure handling

## Code Example

```javascript
// Skeleton: per-tenant cache with TTL and invalidation broadcast
class TenantCache {
  constructor(configServiceUrl, pubSub) {
    this.cache = new Map();
    this.configServiceUrl = configServiceUrl;
    this.pubSub = pubSub;

    this.pubSub.subscribe('invalidate', (tenantId, path) => {
      this.invalidate(tenantId, path);
    });
  }

  async get(tenantId, path) {
    const ttl = await this.getTTL(tenantId);
    const key = `${tenantId}:${path}`;
    const entry = this.cache.get(key);

    if (entry && Date.now() < entry.expiresAt) {
      return entry.value;
    }
    return null;
  }

  async set(tenantId, path, value) {
    const ttl = await this.getTTL(tenantId);
    const key = `${tenantId}:${path}`;
    this.cache.set(key, {
      value,
      expiresAt: Date.now() + ttl
    });
  }

  async invalidate(tenantId, path) {
    const key = `${tenantId}:${path}`;
    this.cache.delete(key);
  }

  async broadcastInvalidation(tenantId, path) {
    await this.pubSub.publish('invalidate', tenantId, path);
  }

  async getTTL(tenantId) {
    // Fetch from central config service
    const config = await fetch(`${this.configServiceUrl}/tenants/${tenantId}`);
    return config.cacheTTL || 300;
  }
}
```

